%S A397408 0,1,2,5,3,6,11,8,13,21,16,24,32,19,14,9,4,7,12,17,25,33,20,15,10,18,
%T A397408 26,34,42,29,37,50,63,76,89,68,55,47,39,31,23,36,28,41,54,67,80,93,72,
%U A397408 59,46,38,30,22,35,27,40,53,66,79,92,71,58,45,61,48,56,43
%N A397408 Shortest path indices during walk over Archimedean spiral lattice with divergence angle equal to golden angle and starting at the center.
%C A397408 Start with spiral lattice generated by (k * cos(k*theta), k * sin(k*theta)) for theta being the golden angle (A131988) and k = 0, 1, 2, 3, ... .
%C A397408 Next, starting at point (0,0), move to the closest unvisited point. a(n) is the index k corresponding to the point reached after n moves.
%C A397408 Will all points of the lattice be visited?
%H A397408 Witold Tatkiewicz, <a href="/A397408/a397408.png">Illustration for n=0..75</a>.
%H A397408 Witold Tatkiewicz, <a href="/A397408/a397408_1.png">Illustration for n=0..75 zoomed in</a>.
%e A397408 Below is table of Cartesian coordinates of the first 10 points:
%e A397408   k   x(k)   y(k)
%e A397408   ---------------
%e A397408   0   0.00   0.00
%e A397408   1  -0.74   0.68
%e A397408   2   0.17  -1.99
%e A397408   3   1.83   2.38
%e A397408   4  -3.94  -0.70
%e A397408   5   4.22  -2.68
%e A397408   6  -1.56   5.79
%e A397408   7  -3.23  -6.21
%e A397408   8   7.51   2.74
%e A397408   9  -8.32   3.43
%e A397408 We start at point (0.00, 0.00) that corresponds to k = 0, therefore a(0) = 0.
%e A397408 Unvisited point closest to (0.00, 0.00) is (-0.74, 0.68) corresponding to k = 1, therefore a(1) = 1.
%e A397408 Unvisited point closest to (-0.74, 0.68) is (0.17, -1.99) corresponding to k = 2, therefore a(2) = 2.
%e A397408 Unvisited point closest to (0.17, -1.99) is (4.22, -2.68) corresponding to k = 5, therefore a(3) = 5.
%e A397408 Unvisited point closest to (4.22, -2.68) is (1.83, 2.38) corresponding to k = 3, therefore a(4) = 3.
%Y A397408 Cf. A000045, A000796, A001622, A131988, A396911.
